title: Grateful Dead Live at Knickerbocker Arena on 1993-03-27
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Bertha, The Same Thing, Peggy-O, Queen Jane Approximately, Broken Arrow, Loose Lucy, Cassidy, Casey Jones

Set 2

Eyes Of The World-> Estimated Prophet-> Comes A Time-> Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel, All Along The Watchtower, The Days Between, One More Saturday Night, E: I Fought The Law

reviews.review_text: It's nice and sad Well the monsoons have hit india and I can't get my ass out of the house cause the road outside is flooded (mainly with bright red mud)...nothing better to do so what the hell why not try some 93...listen with no or very little expectations and u won't be disappointed..the emotion in jerry's voice is just heart rendering....man, he has his way with sad songs...the set list is terrific too, broken arrow, days between, lazy river road, comes a time and a pretty decent eyes of the world...so if your stuck at home on a rainy day with a disposition for some sad soothing music (yes, both sad and soothing in the same sentence :-)) then you'd like to give this a try...

Stuck inside a mobile. Even with all the shows where I was inside, this night stands out because I couldn't get in. A 2 hour drive from my house and I was stuck in the parking lot missing the Casey Jones. Glad to have it now.
